 <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The Ring of the Light - An Overview<br>
<br>
The Ring of the Light is a good and neutral aligned guild for Everquest on the Firiona Vie server. Role-playing is strongly encouraged. We are a group of individuals dedicated to stopping the spread of evil across Norrath, as well as dedicated to each other. Our Light is the light of reason, we believe that there is enough evil existing on Norrath that we do not need to create any more by warring with other guilds. Each member is family and has an equal voice. To ease decision-making we have an elected leader and Council of representatives who serve the guild. The Ring is a member of The Fellowship, an alliance of eight similar guilds of neutral and good alignments. We expect a high level of conduct from our players. To learn more, please see the code of conduct for the guild.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub189.ezboard.com/fringofthelightfrm15" target="top">pub189.ezboard.com/fringofthelightfrm15</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
There are many guilds and many ways to play the game, we believe that no one way or one guild is better or right for everyone.<br>
<br>
We exist to be a family, a network of people who are concerned about and help each other.<br>
<br>
We will never be an Uber guild. If you consider yourself a power player, you will probably not be happy with us. <br>
<br>
If your purpose of joining a guild is to receive gear, weapons or money without earning them, you will be severely disappointed in us.<br>
<br>
We will never be the biggest guild, but we will have some of the best people in the game.<br>
<br>
Currently our age requirement is 10 Seasons, but the majority of our members range in age from 40-60, with quite a nice grouping of 20's to 30-somethings.<br>
<br>
Can we always provide you with a group? No, we aren't even going to try, but we do encourage guild mates to group with each other, and we are part of the Fellowship, which provides other opportunities for grouping and meeting new friends. <br>
<br>
If ye have further questions, please feel free ta contact one of us while we're awake in Norrath. <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"> /who &quot;Ring of the Light&quot; all.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
